   {:e #blake3 "e0ec5a9ad0cdfe3bb3166f8483843eae622b3a8589133c1193c1a6b1068d9a74" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The 5 innate concept descriptions (concept.rs INNATE_CONCEPTS, line 861) are semantically broad. With model2vec, 'Parts of the system and their boundaries — packages, modules, crates, files, services' matches any software observation. The descriptions need to emphasize the DISTINGUISHING feature of each concept so model2vec can separate them.\n\nAPPROACH: Revise INNATE_CONCEPTS descriptions to be more discriminative:\n\nFrom:\n  ('components', 'Parts of the system and their boundaries — packages, modules, crates, files, services')\n  ('dependencies', 'How parts relate to each other — imports, calls, data flow, coupling, interfaces')\n  ('invariants', 'What should hold true — rules, constraints, assertions, contracts, specifications')\n  ('patterns', 'Recurring regularities — idioms, conventions, architectures, protocols, templates')\n  ('anomalies', 'Deviations from expectations — bugs, inconsistencies, violations, surprises, gaps')\n\nTo:\n  ('components', 'Discrete isolated parts: individual packages, modules, files, and services as bounded units')\n  ('dependencies', 'Relationships and connections: imports, function calls, data flow paths between modules')\n  ('invariants', 'Rules and constraints: assertions that must hold, contracts to verify, specifications to enforce')\n  ('patterns', 'Recurring structures: repeated idioms, architectural conventions, protocol templates')\n  ('anomalies', 'Defects and surprises: bugs, violations, inconsistencies, unexpected behaviors, test failures')\n\nKey changes: (1) Remove shared vocabulary ('system', 'boundaries') that appears in multiple descriptions. (2) Lead with the distinguishing noun ('Discrete isolated parts' vs 'Relationships and connections' vs 'Rules and constraints'). (3) Remove the em-dash pattern that makes all descriptions syntactically identical to model2vec.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) Each innate concept has a revised description. (B) The descriptions share minimal vocabulary overlap. (C) braid init on a fresh store produces concepts with the new descriptions. (D) C8 compliance: descriptions still work for non-software domains. (E) All existing tests pass (they use HashEmbedder which is vocab-insensitive).\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (INNATE_CONCEPTS constant, line 861)" :op :assert}
